{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Eph|6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","chapter":6,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":1,"text":"Children, obey your parents in the Lord, because this is right.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":2,"text":"Honor your father and mother, which is the first commandment with a promise,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":3,"text":"so that it may go well with you and that you may have a long life in the land.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":4,"text":"Fathers, don’t stir up anger in your children, but bring them up in the training and instruction of the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":5,"text":"Slaves, obey your human masters with fear and trembling, in the sincerity of your heart, as you would Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":6,"text":"Don’t work only while being watched, as people-pleasers, but as slaves of Christ, doing God’s will from your heart.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":7,"text":"Serve with a good attitude, as to the Lord and not to people,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":8,"text":"knowing that whatever good each one does, slave or free, he will receive this back from the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":9,"text":"And masters, treat your slaves the same way, without threatening them, because you know that both their Master and yours is in heaven, and there is no favoritism with him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":10,"text":"Finally, be strengthened by the Lord and by his vast strength.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":11,"text":"Put on the full armor of God so that you can stand against the schemes of the devil.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":12,"text":"For our struggle is not against flesh and blood, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the cosmic powers of this darkness, against evil, spiritual forces in the heavens.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":13,"text":"For this reason take up the full armor of God, so that you may be able to resist in the evil day, and having prepared everything, to take your stand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":14,"text":"Stand, therefore, with truth like a belt around your waist, righteousness like armor on your chest,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":15,"text":"and your feet sandaled with readiness for the gospel of peace.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":16,"text":"In every situation take up the shield of faith with which you can extinguish all the flaming arrows of the evil one.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":17,"text":"Take the helmet of salvation and the sword of the Spirit —which is the word of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":18,"text":"Pray at all times in the Spirit with every prayer and request, and stay alert with all perseverance and intercession for all the saints.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":19,"text":"Pray also for me, that the message may be given to me when I open my mouth to make known with boldness the mystery of the gospel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":20,"text":"For this I am an ambassador in chains. Pray that I might be bold enough to speak about it as I should.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":21,"text":"Tychicus, our dearly loved brother and faithful servant in the Lord, will tell you all the news about me so that you may be informed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":22,"text":"I am sending him to you for this very reason, to let you know how we are and to encourage your hearts.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":23,"text":"Peace to the brothers and sisters, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":6,"verse":24,"text":"Grace be with all who have undying love for our Lord Jesus Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","chapter":6,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,10,21,23],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Children and Parents"},{"beforeVerse":5,"text":"Slaves and Masters"},{"beforeVerse":10,"text":"Christian Warfare"},{"beforeVerse":21,"text":"Paul’s Farewell"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:6:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Children, obey "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 1:8","book":"Pro","chapter":1,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 6:20","book":"Pro","chapter":6,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 23:22","book":"Pro","chapter":23,"verse":22,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 3:20","book":"Col","chapter":3,"verse":20,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" your parents in the Lord, because this is right. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Pr 1:8","book":"Pro","chapter":1,"verse":8},{"label":"Pr 6:20","book":"Pro","chapter":6,"verse":20},{"label":"Pr 23:22","book":"Pro","chapter":23,"verse":22},{"label":"Col 3:20","book":"Col","chapter":3,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-